# Issue registration

When work is **out of slice scope**, **follow-up**, or **blocked on another track**, agents MUST register a GitHub issue and MUST NOT silently defer or expand the current task.

Canonical procedure: [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md#issue-registration).

## MUST register

- Tech debt or refactor outside current acceptance criteria
- Bug found in unrelated area during scoped work
- Generic pattern that belongs in [flows](https://github.com/alicemq/flows/issues) (not product domain)
- Blocker another agent should own (missing access, cross-repo change)
- Hotfix skip: open follow-up issue after merge

## MAY fix inline (no new issue)

- Typo in a file already changed in the same PR
- Lint or gate failure directly caused by your edit

## Procedure

1. **Choose repo** — product issue for product work; flows issue for generic templates, components, or handbook patterns.
2. **Create issue** — prefer `gh issue create`; use debt template when installed (`agent-handbook/templates/.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/debt.yml`).
3. **Labels** — `source:ai` plus `type:debt`, `type:bug`, `type:feature`, `type:docs`, or `type:security`; add `priority:p0`–`p2` when known.
4. **Body** — include: user story, dev story (scope, acceptance criteria, out of scope), **Found during:** `#parent` or PR link, **Suggested owner:** Dev | QA | DevOps | security follow-up.
5. **Report** — add `Debt filed: #N` (or equivalent) in PR description or coordinator synthesis; do not implement unless PO adds to the active slice.

## Anti-patterns

- Expanding scope to "fix while here" without PO approval or a new issue
- Leaving debt only in chat or comments with no tracker entry
- One subagent issue bundling multiple unrelated follow-ups
